> **Theory Box: Why This Is the Foundation of Agents**
>
> Look at what just happened: the LLM *decided* it needed info, *chose* a tool, *specified* arguments, *processed* the result, and *decided* whether to call another tool or answer. This loop — call, observe, decide — is the foundation of every AI agent. Module 1 of the Agentic AI series builds directly on this pattern.

